elements.title: Parliament Hill
elements.contents: ... that the site of Parliament Hill (pictured) was previously called Barrack Hill and had been intended for development as a major military base?

elements.title: Wanamaker expedition
elements.contents: ... that the third Wanamaker expedition, led by Joseph K. Dixon, travelled at least 20,000 miles (32,000 km) and visited 89 Native American tribes?

elements.title: Laura Robinson
elements.contents: ... that Laura Robinson invented Canada's best-selling board game before becoming a successful actress and television producer?

elements.title: Alkalihalobacillus
elements.contents: ... that some species of bacteria in the genus Alkalihalobacillus live in hypersaline lakes while others are added to laundry detergent?

elements.title: Philip Ewell
elements.contents: ... that music theorist Philip Ewell received "anti-Black statements and personal ad hominem attacks" following his claim that Western music theory is shaped by a "white racial frame"?

elements.title: Murray Dowey
elements.contents: ... that Murray Dowey was a clerk and typist for the Toronto Transit Commission before being the goaltender for Canada's gold-medal-winning hockey team at the 1948 Winter Olympics?

elements.title: Walter Bean Grand River Trail
elements.contents: ... that the Walter Bean Grand River Trail was named after Walter Bean, who created the idea of a continuous trail through the Waterloo region?

elements.title: Toman
elements.contents: ... that Toman helped popularize genderless fashion in Japan?
